00:44.566 --> 00:46.089
your daughter is
a published author. [chuckles]

00:46.176 --> 00:49.397
What?Molly, that is so exciting.

00:49.484 --> 00:51.660
Getting paid
for what you love to do.

00:51.747 --> 00:54.010
You and my dealer,
two of the lucky few.

00:55.794 --> 00:57.100
Well, it's just
a little article,

00:57.187 --> 00:59.320
you know, published
on a national blog.

00:59.407 --> 01:01.409
[chuckles]
JOYCE:
Wow.

01:01.496 --> 01:02.845
Sure shut up
all those people

01:02.932 --> 01:04.020
who never thought
you could do it.

01:04.107 --> 01:07.763
Who?Names aren't important.

01:07.850 --> 01:09.373
Well, I had my doubts myself.

01:09.460 --> 01:11.245
Sometimes I'd look at Mike
and just think,

01:11.332 --> 01:13.421
"Oh, you poor, sweet,
supportive fool.

01:13.508 --> 01:15.814
We are so screwed."

01:15.901 --> 01:17.077
Screwed? I thought you said
we were right on schedule.

01:17.164 --> 01:20.689
Well, we can laugh about it now.

01:20.776 --> 01:23.387
How much money
are we talking about?

01:23.474 --> 01:25.911
Not about the money;
it's about what it represents.

01:25.998 --> 01:28.262
Does is represent more than
the $3,800 you owe your mother?

01:28.349 --> 01:31.961
'Cause we'd like to take
a Carnival cruise this summer.

01:32.048 --> 01:34.833
You don't get
reimbursed monetarily.

01:34.920 --> 01:36.357
So squat.

01:36.444 --> 01:37.401
Yes, and I'm fine with that,

01:37.488 --> 01:40.012
because it's about exposure.

01:40.100 --> 01:42.841
Look at you, exposing
yourself on the Internet.

01:42.928 --> 01:44.713
JOYCE:
So, what's the
article about?

01:44.800 --> 01:46.628
Yeah, I'd like to read it.

01:46.715 --> 01:47.672
Or pretend to.

01:47.759 --> 01:50.371
You know, to be supportive.

01:50.458 --> 01:52.112
